\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Solution.

\series default
 We know that an infinitesimal rotation of a rigid body can be thought of
 as the result of three sucessive infinitesimal rotations whose angular
 velocities have, magnitudes given by 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{\phi},\dot{\theta},\dot{\psi}$
\end_inset

, now, assuming that 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{\phi},\omega_{\theta}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{\psi}$
\end_inset

 are the corresponding angular velocity vectors, then the general angular
 velocity vector will be 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega=\omega_{\phi}+\omega_{\theta}+\omega_{\psi},
\]

\end_inset

due to the fact that the angular velocity 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega$
\end_inset

 depends linearly on 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{\phi},\dot{\theta},\dot{\psi}$
\end_inset

, it follows that, in order to find the general form taken by 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega$
\end_inset

 we can fix a pair of Euler angles at a time, determine the angular velocity
 associated with the variation of the third angle and then add the results.
 Now, with this information at hand, our goal is to express the general
 angular velocity 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega$
\end_inset

 as a linear combination of some rotations of the velocities 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{\phi},\dot{\theta},\dot{\psi}$
\end_inset

.
 And in the case for the angular velocity in the axes fixed in space, we
 have, for the angular velocity 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{\psi}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega_{\psi}=\mathcal{A}^{-1}\left(\begin{array}{c}
0\\
0\\
\dot{\psi}
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{A}^{-1}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
\cos\psi\cos\phi-\cos\theta\sin\phi\sin\psi & -\sin\psi\cos\phi-\cos\theta\cos\phi\cos\psi & \sin\theta\sin\phi\\
\cos\psi\sin\phi+\cos\theta\sin\phi\sin\psi & -\sin\psi\sin\phi+\cos\theta\cos\phi\cos\psi & -\sin\theta\cos\phi\\
\sin\psi\sin\theta & -\cos\psi\cos\phi & \cos\theta
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

thus
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega_{\psi}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
\cos\psi\cos\phi-\cos\theta\sin\phi\sin\psi & -\sin\psi\cos\phi-\cos\theta\cos\phi\cos\psi & \sin\theta\sin\phi\\
\cos\psi\sin\phi+\cos\theta\sin\phi\sin\psi & -\sin\psi\sin\phi+\cos\theta\cos\phi\cos\psi & -\sin\theta\cos\phi\\
\sin\psi\sin\theta & -\cos\psi\cos\phi & \cos\theta
\end{array}\right)\left(\begin{array}{c}
0\\
0\\
\dot{\psi}
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\implies\omega_{\psi}=\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{\psi}\sin\theta\sin\phi\\
-\dot{\psi}\sin\theta\cos\phi\\
\dot{\psi}\cos\theta
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

moving on the calcualtions, for the angular velocity 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{\theta}$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega_{\theta}=\mathcal{B}\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{\theta}\\
0\\
0
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{D}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
\cos\phi & \sin\phi & 0\\
-\sin\phi & \cos\phi & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

thus
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega_{\theta}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
\cos\phi & \sin\phi & 0\\
-\sin\phi & \cos\phi & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right)\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{\theta}\\
0\\
0
\end{array}\right)=\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{\theta}\cos\phi\\
-\dot{\theta}\sin\phi\\
0
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\implies\omega_{\theta}=\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{\theta}\cos\phi\\
-\dot{\theta}\sin\phi\\
0
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

and finnaly, for 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{\phi}$
\end_inset

 this is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega_{\phi}=\mathcal{B}\left(\begin{array}{c}
0\\
0\\
\dot{\phi}
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{D}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
\cos\psi & \sin\psi & 0\\
-\sin\psi & \cos\psi & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

thus 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega_{\phi}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
\cos\psi & \sin\psi & 0\\
-\sin\psi & \cos\psi & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right)\left(\begin{array}{c}
0\\
0\\
\dot{\phi}
\end{array}\right)=\left(\begin{array}{c}
0\\
0\\
\dot{\phi}
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

and with this information, we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\omega=\omega_{\phi}+\omega_{\theta}+\omega_{\psi},
\]

\end_inset

ot in component, notation
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(\begin{array}{c}
\omega_{x}\\
\omega_{y}\\
\omega_{z}
\end{array}\right)=\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{\theta}\cos\phi\\
-\dot{\theta}\sin\phi\\
0
\end{array}\right)+\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{\psi}\sin\theta\sin\phi\\
-\dot{\psi}\sin\theta\cos\phi\\
\dot{\psi}\cos\theta
\end{array}\right)+\left(\begin{array}{c}
0\\
0\\
\dot{\phi}
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\therefore\left(\begin{array}{c}
\omega_{x}\\
\omega_{y}\\
\omega_{z}
\end{array}\right)=\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{\theta}\cos\phi+\dot{\psi}\sin\theta\sin\phi\\
-\dot{\theta}\sin\phi-\dot{\psi}\sin\theta\cos\phi\\
\dot{\psi}\cos\theta+\dot{\phi}
\end{array}\right),
\]

\end_inset

just as we wanted.
